  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In the [stackLimitPush31_1025](https://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/develop/src/GeneralStateTestsFiller/stMemoryTest/stackLimitPush31_1025Filler.json) test, IIUC its intention is to check when reaching stack depth limit, which should be 1024, the transaction will fail with stack overflow error. However in the [expect](https://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/develop/src/GeneralStateTestsFiller/stMemoryTest/stackLimitPush31_1025Filler.json#L29) section, it expects the nonce of the account to increase even the transaction should fail, why is it the case?",
