    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The transaction will fail because of a stack overflow error. However, the transaction will still succeed and will be logged (the nonce will be increased). Otherwise, it would be possible to \"conditionally\" send transactions: if X happens then stack overflow and the tx did not happen, but if Y happen execute the transaction. \r\n\r\nThis is the same as if a transaction goes OOG. You sign a transaction, it should execute, and once it is executed it should be logged. If the EOA (externally owned account) wishes to execute it again, then resign the transaction with another nonce.\r\n\r\n(This is all part of replay protection). So, this is not a bug (someone else confirm this please).",
